  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 trigger)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research contexts to predict hemolysis indices for centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD model targets absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors; seven factors were formally assessed and six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite the high model risk level, the assessment team concluded that the achieved credibility evidence is sufficient for the intended regulatory submission under the Minimal profile, accepting the package with documented residual uncertainty. No structured Context of Use object is bound to this assurance unit; the intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative description.",
